# Node.js API Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Node.js 20+ with TypeScript
- Express or Fastify
- Prisma + PostgreSQL
- Zod for validation
- Jest / Vitest for testing

## Architecture
- Controllers handle HTTP, nothing else
- Services contain business logic
- Repositories handle data access
- Middlewares for cross-cutting concerns (auth, logging, rate-limit)

## Request Handling
- Validate all input with Zod before processing
- Never trust req.body shape — always parse and validate
- Return consistent error shapes: `{ error: { code, message, details? } }`
- HTTP status codes must be semantically correct

## TypeScript
- Strict mode required
- Explicit return types on all functions
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type narrowing
- Async functions must be wrapped in try/catch or use a result type

## Security
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
- Sanitize user input before DB writes
- Use parameterized queries — never string-interpolate SQL
- Rate-limit all public endpoints

## Error Handling
- Custom error classes extending Error
- Always include error context in logs
- Never expose stack traces in production responses
